 but that's not the interesting bit about it.

00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:31.760
 Within that match was the longest single rally

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:33.880
 of tennis ever to occur.

00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:36.600
 So this was September 24th, 1984,

00:07:36.600 --> 00:07:39.880
 and this was the longest in terms of a pro match,

00:07:39.880 --> 00:07:42.200
 longest rally, how many shots do you think

00:07:42.200 --> 00:07:43.520
 this rally went for?

00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:45.920
 - Shots, what?

00:07:45.920 --> 00:07:47.240
 - 160.

00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:48.720
 - Yeah, 110.

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:50.360
 - Pretty good, pretty good.

00:07:50.360 --> 00:07:52.760
 - I'm gonna say a hundred.

00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:56.920
 - It lasted 29 minutes and it went for 643 shots.

00:07:56.920 --> 00:07:59.320
 - Oh my God.

00:07:59.320 --> 00:08:03.440
 Serena Williams has won matches in shorter time than that.

00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:06.400
 - Yeah, it was between Vicki Nelson Dunbar

00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:10.680
 and Jean Hepner, and it was a set point for Hepner,

00:08:10.680 --> 00:08:14.200
 and it was in a tie break at the end of the match,

00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:16.600
 and it went 29 minutes long,

00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:20.800
 and Vicki Nelson managed to take it on the 643rd shot.

00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:21.640
 - Oh my God.

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:22.680
 - Jean of the match.

00:08:22.680 --> 00:08:24.920
 - Oh, she would never have recovered for Jean.

00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:26.520
 - Oh, it was horrible.

